  "rationale": "<p>Choice D is correct. The first line has equation y = -2x/5 + 16/5. The second line has equation y = x - 1. Setting these equal: x - 1 = -2x/5 + 16/5, so 5x - 5 = -2x + 16, giving 7x = 21 and x = 3. Then y = 2. The intersection is (3, 2). The other choices give points on only one of the lines.</p>",
